description: Values of cototient function for A053577.
comments: Except for 2^0=1, there are only finitely many values of k such that cototient(k) = 2^m for fixed m.
example: For p prime, cototient[p]=1. Smallest values for which cototient[x]=2^w are 6,12,24,96,192,..,49152 for w=2,3,4,5,6,...,15
author: _Labos Elemer_, Jan 18 2000
